The objectives of this study are: - To evaluate the ability of the Methacetin Breath Test (MBT) to detect hepatic decompensation events - To evaluate the relationship between liver Biopsy and clinical outcome and show that the MBT has a better predictive ability of clinical outcome than liver biopsy.

 - To evaluate the ability of the MBT to predict each of the individual liver related complications.

